# Tuning spark.sql.shuffle.partitions

## The default is 200 — sized for big clusters

- On `local[*]` with 8 cores → ~192 mostly-empty partitions + scheduling overhead
- On a big dataset → far too **few** → oversized partitions that spill

## The fix

- **Local** — **2–4× core count**
- **Cluster** — the **128–256 MB-per-partition** rule on the largest post-shuffle dataset
- `spark.conf.set("spark.sql.shuffle.partitions", n)`

## Note

- **AQE now coalesces** empty post-shuffle partitions → matters most when the default is too **small**
